events.name: New Orleans Pelicans at Detroit Pistons

headlines.description: — Brandon Ingram scored 26 points, Jonas Valanciunas added 13 points and 13 rebounds, and the New Orleans Pelicans overcame a 15-point deficit to beat the Detroit Pistons 111-101 on Tuesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Ingram has 26, Pelicans rally for 111-101 win over Pistons

headlines.description: — Giannis Antetokounmpo had 33 points, 15 rebounds and 11 assists for his fourth triple-double of the season as the Milwaukee Bucks beat Washington 112-98 on Tuesday night to hand the Wizards their sixth straight loss.
headlines.shortLinkText: Antetokounmpo's triple-double helps Bucks top Wizards 112-98

headlines.description: — Gary Trent Jr. scored 33 points, Pascal Siakam had 16 points and 14 rebounds and the Toronto Raptors won their third straight game, beating the Miami Heat 110-106 on Tuesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Trent Jr. tops 30 for 5th straight game as Raptors beat Heat

headlines.description: — DeMar DeRozan scored 29 points, Zach LaVine added 24 and the Chicago Bulls beat the Orlando Magic 126-115 on Tuesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Bulls hold off Magic's 4th quarter rally for 126-115 win

headlines.description: — Jarred Vanderbilt scored 18 points against his former team, Taurean Prince had 23 and the Minnesota Timberwolves’ bench led the way in a 130-115 victory over the Denver Nuggets on Tuesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Wolves' bench leads the way in 130-115 win against Nuggets

events.name: Golden State Warriors at San Antonio Spurs

headlines.description: — Jordan Poole had 31 points, including a go-ahead 3-pointer with 17.9 seconds remaining, and the short-handed Golden State Warriors beat the San Antonio Spurs 124-120 on Tuesday night for their seventh straight victory.
headlines.shortLinkText: Short-handed Warriors stun Spurs 124-120 to extend streak

headlines.description: — Every opposing team knows that Phoenix Suns guard Devin Booker can score points in bunches. They also know about Chris Paul's elite passing and mid-range game, along with Deandre Ayton's low-post scoring ability.
headlines.shortLinkText: Suns roll to 11th straight victory, beat Nets 121-111
